3 (A) (1) IN THIS SECTION THE FOLLOWING WORDS HAVE THE MEANINGS
4 INDICATED.
5 (2) “LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY” HAS THE MEANING STATED IN §
6 3–201 OF THE PUBLIC SAFETY ARTICLE.
7 (3) “LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENT” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL WHO IS
8 CERTIFIED BY THE MARYLAND POLICE TRAINING AND STANDARDS COMMISSION
9 UNDER § 3–209 OF THE PUBLIC SAFETY ARTICLE.
10 (B) IF REQUESTED BY FEDERAL IMMIGRATION AUTHORITIES, A LAW
11 ENFORCEMENT AGENCY, LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENT, OR LOCAL DETENTION
12 FACILITY SHALL:
13 (1) NOTIFY FEDERAL IMMIGRATION AUTHORITIES:
14 (I) THAT THE LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENCY, LAW
15 ENFORCEMENT AGENT, OR LOCAL DETENTION FACILITY HAS TAKEN CUSTODY OF AN
16 INDIVIDUAL WHO IS THE SUBJECT OF AN OUTSTANDING CRIMINAL WARRANT; AND
17 (II) OF THE DETAILS OF THE CUSTODY, INCLUDING, IF
18 APPLICABLE, INFORMATION REGARDING THE PLANNED RELEASE OF THE
19 INDIVIDUAL;
20 (2) RETAIN CUSTODY OF ANY INDIVIDUAL WHO IS THE SUBJECT OF AN
21 OUTSTANDING CRIMINAL WARRANT FOR UP TO 48 HOURS BEYOND THE PLANNED
22 RELEASE OF THE INDIVIDUAL; AND
23 (3) COOPERATE WITH FEDERAL IMMIGRATION AUTHORITIES TO
24 ARRANGE FOR THE TRANSFER OF ANY INDIVIDUAL WHO IS THE SUBJECT OF AN
25 OUTSTANDING CRIMINAL WARRANT TO FEDERAL IMMIGRATION AUTHORITIES TO
26 DETERMINE WHETHER THE INDIVIDUAL IS A PRIORITY FOR REMOVAL, CONSISTENT
27 WITH THE ENFORCEMENT PRIORITIES OF THE DEPARTMENT OF HOMELAND
28 SECURITY.
29 (C) DURING AN INVESTIGATION UNDER THIS SECTION, A LAW
30 ENFORCEMENT AGENCY, LAW ENFORCEMENT AGENT, OR LOCAL DETENTION
31 FACILITY SHALL PROVIDE AN INTERPRETER FOR ANY INDIVIDUAL WHO REQUIRES
32 ONE TO EFFECTIVELY COMMUNICATE.

HOUSE BILL 1307 3
1 (D) THE STATE, A UNIT OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT, A COUNTY SHERIFF, OR AN
2 AGENCY OF THE STATE OR A UNIT OF LOCAL GOVERNMENT MAY NOT ADOPT,
3 IMPLEMENT, OR ENFORCE ANY POLICY THAT LIMITS OR PROHIBITS COOPERATION
4 WITH FEDERAL IMMIGRATION AUTHORITIES IN THE INVESTIGATION OR
5 APPREHENSION OF INDIVIDUALS NOT LAWFULLY PRESENT IN THE UNITED STATES
6 WHO ARE THE SUBJECT OF OUTSTANDING CRIMINAL WARRANTS.
7 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
8 October 1, 2025.

